# üêß Linux & Docker Short Flags Cheat Sheet

A quick reference guide for commonly used short command-line flags in **Docker** and **Linux**.

---

## üê≥ Docker Command Flags

| Short Flag | Long Form | Description | Example |
|-------------|------------|--------------|----------|
| `-d` | `--detach` | Run container in the background (detached mode) | `docker run -d nginx` |
| `-it` | `--interactive --tty` | Run interactively with terminal access | `docker run -it ubuntu bash` |
| `-p` | `--publish` | Map container port to host port (`host:container`) | `-p 8080:80` |
| `-e` | `--env` | Set environment variable inside container | `-e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root` |
| `-v` | `--volume` | Mount host directory or file inside container | `-v /data:/var/lib/mysql` |
| *(none)* | `--name` | Assign a custom name to the container | `--name my-container` |
| *(none)* | `--rm` | Automatically remove container when it stops | `docker run --rm ubuntu` |
| `-a` | `--attach` | Attach to container‚Äôs output streams | `docker run -a stdout nginx` |
| `-f` | `--force` | Force an action (e.g., image removal) | `docker rmi -f image_id` |

---

## üß† Common Linux Command Flags

| Short Flag | Description | Example |
|-------------|--------------|----------|
| `-l` | Long listing format (detailed info) | `ls -l` |
| `-a` | Show all files, including hidden | `ls -a` |
| `-h` | Human-readable output (e.g. file sizes) | `ls -lh` |
| `-r` | Reverse order | `ls -lr` |
| `-R` | Recursive (include subdirectories) | `ls -R` |
| `-f` | Force operation (ignore warnings) | `rm -f file.txt` |
| `-i` | Interactive mode (ask before action) | `rm -i file.txt` |
| `-v` | Verbose mode (show actions) | `cp -v file1 file2` |
| `-t` | Sort by time (in `ls`) or allocate TTY (in Docker) | `ls -lt`, `docker run -t` |
| `-n` | Numbered output (like line numbers) | `cat -n file.txt` |

---

